Differential diagnosis . The new species is most similar to
Scutacarus radiculatus Mahunka, 1969
, described from Bolivia ( Mahunka 1969 ), by the absence of the claw on tibiotarsus I and the short, thick dorsal hysterosomal setae. It can be distinguished from the latter by setae 4 b more than two times longer than 4 a (vs. subequal in
S. radiculatus
), by smooth setae ps 1 (vs. distinctly barbed in
S. radiculatus
), and by setae ps 3 distinctly separated from ps 2 (vs. ps 3 situated close to ps
2 in
S . radiculatus
).
